   <documentation>
      <row>
         <Docu><![CDATA[= Action name =
PCK.AUTOMIC_SERVICENOW.PUB.ACTION.CHECK_FIELD_VALUE

= General description =
This action checks if given field and value exist in the given table or not.

= Reference link =
https://docs.servicenow.com/bundle/orlando-application-development/page/integrate/inbound-rest/concept/c_TableAPI.html#r_TableAPI-GET

= Inputs =
* Table Name*  :  Specify the name of the table containing the record. E.g. change_request
* Field Name*  :  Provide field name to check. E.g. state
* Field Value* :  Provide field value to check. E.g. 1

= Failure Conditions =
* If connection parameters are not correct.
* If invalid value provided in Table Name, Field name, or Field value parameter.

= Behavior = 
* If invalid values provided to the input fields, action will fail.
 
= Return Value =
* UC4RB_SN_RESPONSE#     : Array of the field value. e.g: for the state field value -5
* UC4RB_SN_RESPONSE_VAL# : Array of the field display value. e.g: for the state field value -5 and display value new

= Outputs =
* Return code is 0 in case of success.
* Return code is non-zero in case of failure.

= Rollback =
(none)

= Logging =
logs will be displayed in the AE report.

= Example =
Table Name* : incident
Field Name* : state
Field Value*: 1
]]></Docu>
      </row>
   </documentation>
